<article class="element-copy">
	<header id="formatting">
		<h3>Text Formatting</h3>
	</header>
	<p>Please note these are all inline elements, so please use them in sentences (<code>&lt;p></code>). The excepting is the anchor tag, which officially can be a block element in HTML5</p>
	<section class="element-one">
		<p>Spans are cool, you can just wrap em around anything inline and style <span>willy nilly</span></p>
		<pre class="language-markup"><button class="icon-before i-copy">Copy to Clipboard</button><code>&lt;span>Add a class for styling&lt;/span></code></pre>
	</section>
	<section class="element-one">
		<p><span class="feature-text">Featured text. For that extra special copy.</span> Add a class of <code>feature-text</code> to a span to make text bold and italic.</p>
		<pre class="language-markup"><button class="icon-before i-copy">Copy to Clipboard</button><code>&lt;span class="feature-text">Featured text&lt;/span></code></pre>
	</section>
	<section class="element-one">
		<p>This sentence uses the <strong>strong</strong> tag.</p>
		<pre class="language-markup"><button class="icon-before i-copy">Copy to Clipboard</button><code>&lt;strong>This is important&lt;/strong></code></pre>
	</section>
	<section class="element-one">
		<p>This sentence <b>uses the b tag</b>, it styles like strong but has no semantic meaning.</p>
		<pre class="language-markup"><button class="icon-before i-copy">Copy to Clipboard</button><code>&lt;b>I'm a fake strong&lt;/b></code></pre>
	</section>
	<section class="element-one">
		<p>This sentence uses the <em>emphasis</em> tag.</p>
		<pre class="language-markup"><button class="icon-before i-copy">Copy to Clipboard</button><code>&lt;em>This is emphasised&lt;/em></code></pre>
	</section>
	<section class="element-one">
		<p>This sentence <i>uses the i tag</i>, it styles text italic like.</p>
		<pre class="language-markup"><button class="icon-before i-copy">Copy to Clipboard</button><code>&lt;i>I'm italic style text&lt;/i></code></pre>
	</section>
	<section class="element-one">
		<p>You'll notice now I'm going to.<br />Break this sentence with a <code>br</code>. These should <strong>not</strong> be used to clear elements.</p>
		<pre class="language-markup"><button class="icon-before i-copy">Copy to Clipboard</button><code>&lt;br /></code></pre>
	</section>
	<section class="element-one">
		<p>This is an <a href="#" rel="external">inline link</a>. Note the <code>rel</code> atrribute :)</p>
		<pre class="language-markup"><button class="icon-before i-copy">Copy to Clipboard</button><code>&lt;a href="#" rel="external">I'm a link&lt;/a></code></pre>
	</section>
	<section class="element-one">
		<p>This is the <del>keep</del> del element</p>
		<pre class="language-markup"><button class="icon-before i-copy">Copy to Clipboard</button><code>&lt;del>Delete this&lt;/del></code></pre>
	</section>
	<section class="element-one">
		<p>I want to be <mark>highlighted</mark></p>
		<pre class="language-markup"><button class="icon-before i-copy">Copy to Clipboard</button><code>&lt;mark>highlight me&lt;/mark></code></pre>
	</section>
	<section class="element-one">
		<p>I'm going to <ins>insert something here</ins>.</p>
		<pre class="language-markup"><button class="icon-before i-copy">Copy to Clipboard</button><code>&lt;ins>inserted&lt;/ins></code></pre>
	</section>
	<section class="element-one">
		<p>This is <dfn title="to describe something">defined</dfn>, hover it.</p>
		<pre class="language-markup"><button class="icon-before i-copy">Copy to Clipboard</button><code>&lt;dfn title="definition here">define&lt;/dfn></code></pre>
	</section>
	<section class="element-one">
		<p>The <abbr title="United Kingdom">UK</abbr> is abbreviated</p>
		<pre class="language-markup"><button class="icon-before i-copy">Copy to Clipboard</button><code>&lt;abbr title="long version here">&lt;/abbr></code></pre>
	</section>
	<section class="element-one">
		<p>If you're writing <code>code</code> you may use this.</p>
		<pre class="language-markup"><button class="icon-before i-copy">Copy to Clipboard</button><code>&lt;code>code here&lt;/code></code></pre>
	</section>
	<section class="element-one">
		<p>So there's a keyboard tag. Press <kbd>Enter</kbd></p>
		<pre class="language-markup"><button class="icon-before i-copy">Copy to Clipboard</button><code>&lt;kbd>Enter&lt;/kbd></code></pre>
	</section>
	<section class="element-one">
		<p>There's also <samp>sample output</samp> from a program.</p>
		<pre class="language-markup"><button class="icon-before i-copy">Copy to Clipboard</button><code>&lt;samp>sample output&lt;/samp></code></pre>
	</section>
	<section class="element-one">
		<p>A simple equation: <var>x</var> = <var>y</var> + 2</p>
		<pre class="language-markup"><button class="icon-before i-copy">Copy to Clipboard</button><code>&lt;var>variable here&lt;/var></code></pre>
	</section>
	<section class="element-one">
		<p>This is <small>tiny</small> text</p>
		<pre class="language-markup"><button class="icon-before i-copy">Copy to Clipboard</button><code>&lt;small>small text&lt;/small></code></pre>
	</section>
	<section class="element-one">
		<p>The <sub>sub text</sub> element</p>
		<pre class="language-markup"><button class="icon-before i-copy">Copy to Clipboard</button><code>&lt;sub>sub text&lt;/sub></code></pre>
	</section>
	<section class="element-one">
		<p>The <sup>sup text</sup> element</p>
		<pre class="language-markup"><button class="icon-before i-copy">Copy to Clipboard</button><code>&lt;sup>sup text&lt;/sup></code></pre>
	</section>
